commit.message: add FAQ regarding supertab not working at all
update README with info on how to access the supertab docs

fix SuperTabLongestHighlight to only move the cursor when the completion popup is visible

fixes #162
Fix syntax in documentation

fix CompleteDone error when manually executing a completion

refs #157

attempt to simplify configuration of completion chainging

update SuperTabChain to set the omni precedence and the default
completion to 1 of the supported defaults and prevent overriding of that
through calls to SuperTabSetCompletionType.

refs #156

update context file completion to handle hidden files/dirs

fixes #155

add support for buffer local SuperTabContextDefaultCompletionType

fixes #153

add tracking of completion mode to alleviate reliance on pumvisible()

for users with a recent version of vim that don't use the completion
menu, add support for tracking when completion mode is started/ended so
that next/previous completions work correctly even when the completion
menu isn't enabled.

Use "inoremap" for "<C-x>" mapping

This is required when `<C-R>` is mapped itself, e.g. with peekaboo:

   i  <C-R>       * <C-O>:call peekaboo#peek(1, 'ctrl-r',  0)<CR>

update html settings when using eclim + php

fixes #144
when disabling cr mapping do to compatibility, update the global var

disable g:SuperTabCrMapping by default

This one feature causes more headaches than any other, with very little
benefit to show for it.

fix supertab <cr> map chaining logic

Looks like the logic for deciding if a cr should be issued by
SelectCompletion has been wrong. Negating the previous logic seems to be
what I had intended (unless there was some other edge case I'm
forgetting).

refs #138

add setting to temporarily override ignorecase

fixes #134
doc: link to supertab-preventcomplete from supertab-mappingtabliteral

add setting for supertab context completion member patterns

refs #133

prevent context file completion on sgml end tags

fixes #133

add note on context omni precedence + completion chaining

refs #131

release fix for possible infinite recursion on <bs>

when s:SuperTabNoCompleteAfter has been modified by the user, then eclim
will remap <bs>. However a recent change[1] modify the s:CompletionReset
code to call the second <bs> char as the mapped version, which if
supertab has it mapped, results in an infinite loop under these
conditions.

fixes #120

[1] https://github.com/ervandew/supertab/commit/c8c1876
Fix a typo.

fix handling of existing non-expr <s-tab> mapping

also remove some code duplication

fixes #123

add support for triggering user's <s-tab> when not completing

fixes #122
fix spelling and whitespace in docs
fix undefined variable 'patch32'
